Guidelines for fixing data tran:
First in the tran report check the margin of setup and hold there we will get the worst setup and hold for particular driver 
Don’t's
Then segregate separately sequential cells and delay buffers and inverters 
If we are swapping the sequential cells then we may expect the clk tran because we are increasing the load of the clk buffer 
Then swapping the delay buffers will leads to degrade the hold violation . 

Checks before fixing the Data Tran 
Net length 
Fanout 
Routing layer 
Drive strength 

Data Tran fixing method's:
VT Swapping 
Upsizing 
Fan out splitting 
On route buffering 
Layer optimization [check for the track availability]
Downsize the load of the driver 
On route buffering [location based ]

Strategy used : [Violations are segregated according to the magnitude ]
If the net length is 120 microns if the driver is HDB*VT06*/BUF/INV > if swapping or upsizing it will reduce the magnitude it won't fix the violation for those cases HDB*06_CAQ*/BUF/INV are replaced because these buffers of 8X can drive 180microns of distance 
If the magnitude is less 5 to 15ps only VT swaps is enough to fix the violations because increasing the drive strength will increase the area of the cell  
If the net length is huge and driver also X10, X12 we can go for on route buffering we can add buffer in the middle of the net 
If the net is routed with lower metal layers check for the track availability and route with higher metal layers 
For sequential cells on route buffering fanout splitting is preferred 
